items.title: Names of Germany's newly born panda twins revealed to the public at Berlin zoo
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Germany's new panda twins now have names — or rather, two names apiece. The two female cubs, born at the Berlin Zoo on Aug. 22, were introduced Friday as Meng Hao and Meng Tian. Alternatively, they answer to the very Berlin names of Leni and Lotti. Read more: https//bit.ly/4giZCXW
(AP video by Pietro De Cristofaro)

items.title: Hundreds in Georgia complain of police brutality at anti-government rallies
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Hundreds of Georgians have complained of police brutality at anti-government rallies held over the past week. Georgian journalist Guram Rogava was one of several hundred who were caught up in the police crackdown on mass protests in the country, triggered by the governing party’s decision to suspend negotiations on joining the European Union. (AP video shot by Kostya Manenkov. Production by Sophiko Megrelidze). Read more: https://bit.ly/4ifvr5X
